The seventh Eclogue reports a vision in which the youthsul Pollux is warned against the ‹langers of the world. and pointed to the safe retreat of Mount Carmel. Here Pollux is commonly supposed to mean Mantuan himself; but the poem was written before he joined his religious order. See, also Introduction, p. 19.
